
'''= “The CF4ESIF is a multi-stakeholder working group established with the aim of exploring the potential of crowdfunding as a blending and match-funding mechanism within the context of the European Cohesion Policy”.'''


URL = https://eurocrowd.org/work-groups/european-structural-investment-funds/?

=Description=

The working group facilitates the dialogue between crowdfunding platforms, regional authorities and European institutions, with the aim of encouraging a joint effort towards the design and implementation of innovative funding schemes.
The outputs of the working group will be the collection of existing best practices of civic crowdfunding in Europe (2018), the implementation of pilot projects where crowdfunding is coupled with ESIF resources (2019), and the publication of guidelines on how to implement similar mechanisms in other European regions (2020).
 
=More information=

More details about the context and objectives of the working group can be found in the White Paper “The European Dimension of Civic Crowdfunding”. https://eurocrowd.org/2017/11/23/european-dimension-civic-crowdfunding-potential-crowdfunding-boosting-economic-social-effectiveness-european-structural-investment-funds/

